Electrical Engineer Job (Electrical Manufacturing), Jakarta, Indonesia
Country:
Indonesia
Function:
Engineering
Industry:
Manufacturing
Position type:
Permanent
Salary:
Negotiable
Created:
02 May 2014
Monroe Consulting Group is recruiting for a multinational company that has been active in the electrical manufacturing sector. Our client is seeking a professional with a background in electrical engineering for the job of Electrical Engineer, to be based in Jakarta, Indonesia. Our client has become a worldwide leader in their industry segment and delivers value to its clients by betting on constant business development, excellence and high-quality human resources. The winning candidate will experience a dynamic, stimulating and international environment, allowing them to grow professionally. The company offers good prospects for career progression.
Key job responsibilities will include:
To help in analysis and interpretation of bid documents
Be in charge of electrical project management
Be in charge of cost estimations in proposals, technical offers and specifications
Maintain relationships with customers and suppliers
Requirements:
Electrical engineering degree
Two to 3 years’ experience in electrical projects
Strong networking in government/private companies
Cost estimation
Excellent team work and organizational skills
Excellent English communication skills, both written and verbal
All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence.